cess_level": "public", "crawl_run_id": "af482bec-40ac-468e-b484-ec46946507fa", "content_hash": "ca86d0b5bbb0c14ad8ea85b823ef9788817cece79b627f42303f1e5207f8e2c0", "page_count": 1, "academic_year": "2024-2025", "needs_ocr": false}}, {"record_id": "5e1e2ab7ab43611b2bc184eb8c58e3d6eca10485fe5d9387d10d028ea2205ee8", "record_type": "table_record", "parent_doc_id": "4715ee79132259e78a7c5ab81fc89b9914b3a1691833352aae1f384368af4775", "source_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/all-policies/criteria-to-maintain-the-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support/", "title": "Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support", "data": {"table_id": "462b37e8abf85ac8aa97b0bfa14cc3a909422c606c045e606e7e5c7932df9f3e", "caption": null, "headers": ["Column 1", "Column 2", "Column 3", "Column 4", "Column 5"], "rows": [["No", "Name", "Type", "Renewal criteria", "Note"], ["1", "Merit-based Scholarships", "Full & 100%", "Renewal is contingent upon: 1. Maintaining a cumulative GPA of 3.2 or higher in the academic year under evaluation (calculated as the average of the two main semesters : Fall and Spring ). 2. Maintain good disciplinary standing: The student must not commit major misconduct (Tier 3) or extremely serious misconduct (Tier 4) as per Student Code of Conduct and Student Academic Integrity . 3. Complete the E . X . C . E . L self-evaluation and meet with the Advisor to discuss the self-evaluatio n.", "If the student does not meet the minimum requirement of academic performance, the two options will be implemented as below: (a) Automatic Downgrade (1 level – based on current scholarship scheme of the academic year) – Applied if the Academic Year GPA is between 0.0 – 2.49 (below good academic standing). (b) Maintain the scholarship with the condition – Applied if the Academic Year GPA is between 2.50 – 3.19 (from good academic standing and above), applicable for Full and 100% scholarships. The students will be granted an additional regular semester to improve their academic and E.X.C.E.L performance. The GPA and E.X.C.E.L performance at the point of re-assessment will be used for further consideration. Note: Special cases may be reviewed by the Committee for consideration."], ["2", "Merit-based Scholarships", "50%; 60%; 70%; 80%; 90%", "Renewal is contingent upon: 1. Maintaining a cumulative GPA of 2.5 or higher in the academic year under evaluation (calculated as the average of the two main semesters : Fall and Spring ). 2. Maintain good disciplinary standing: The student must not commit major misconduct (Tier 3) or extremely serious misconduct (Tier 4) as per Student Code of Conduct and Student Academic Integrity . 3. Complete the E . X . C . E . L self-evaluation and meet with the Advisor to discuss the self-evaluation .", "If the student does not meet the minimum requirement of academic performance, the following option will be implemented as below: Automatic Downgrade (1 level – based on current scholarship scheme of the academic year) – Applied if the Academic Year GPA is between 0.0 – 2.49 (below good academic standing). Note: Special cases may be reviewed by the Committee for consideration."], ["3", "Vinschool-VinUni Scholarship", "5%", "No requirements – automatic renewal", ""], ["4", "Vingroup Family Scholarship", "Adheres to the current policy in effect at the time of application.", "No requirements – automatic renewal", ""], ["5", "WIT (Woman in Tech) Scholarship", "5%", "Automatic renewal if the main entry scholarship is maintained", ""], ["6", "Special Academic Scholarship", "5%", "No requirements – automatic renewal", ""], ["7", "Education Development Aid", "35%", "No requirements – automatic renewal", ""], ["8", "Need-based Financial Aid", "From 50%", "– Maintain the m inimum C GPA 2.0 (Marginal) in the academic year under evaluation (calculated as the average of the two main semesters : Fall and Spring ). – Complete the E . X . C . E . L self-evaluation and meet with the Advisor to discuss on the self-evaluation .", ""]], "row_count": 9, "column_count": 5, "section_path": ["Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support", "3. Criteria to maintain the entry merit-based scholarship and financial aid support"], "page_number": null, "rag_text": "Table: Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support\nColumns: Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 | Column 4 | Column 5\nRow 1: Column 1: No | Column 2: Name | Column 3: Type | Column 4: Renewal criteria | Column 5: Note\nRow 2: Column 1: 1 | Column 2: Merit-based Scholarships | Column 3: Full & 100% | Column 4: Renewal is contingent upon: 1. Maintaining a cumulative GPA of 3.2 or higher in the academic year under evaluation (calculated as the average of the two main semesters : Fall and Spring ). 2. Maintain good disciplinary standing: The student must not commit major misconduct (Tier 3) or extremely serious misconduct (Tier 4) as per Student Code of Conduct and Student Academic Integrity . 3. Complete the E . X . C . E . L self-evaluation and meet with the Advisor to discuss the self-evaluatio n. | Column 5: If the student does not meet the minimum requirement of academic performance, the two options will be implemented as below: (a) Automatic Downgrade (1 level – based on current scholarship scheme of the academic year) – Applied if the Academic Year GPA is between 0.0 – 2.49 (below good academic standing). (b) Maintain the scholarship with the condition – Applied if the Academic Year GPA is between 2.50 – 3.19 (from good academic standing and above), applicable for Full and 100% scholarships. The students will be granted an additional regular semester to improve their academic and E.X.C.E.L performance. The GPA and E.X.C.E.L performance at the point of re-assessment will be used for further consideration. Note: Special cases may be reviewed by the Committee for consideration.\nRow 3: Column 1: 2 | Column 2: Merit-based Scholarships | Column 3: 50%; 60%; 70%; 80%; 90% | Column 4: Renewal is contingent upon: 1. Maintaining a cumulative GPA of 2.5 or higher in the academic year under evaluation (calculated as the average of the two main semesters : Fall and Spring ). 2. Maintain good disciplinary standing: The student must not commit major misconduct (Tier 3) or extremely serious misconduct (Tier 4) as per Student Code of Conduct and Student Academic Integrity . 3. Complete the E . X . C . E . L self-evaluation and meet with the Advisor to discuss the self-evaluation . | Column 5: If the student does not meet the minimum requirement of academic performance, the following option will be implemented as below: Automatic Downgrade (1 level – based on current scholarship scheme of the academic year) – Applied if the Academic Year GPA is between 0.0 – 2.49 (below good academic standing). Note: Special cases may be reviewed by the Committee for consideration.\nRow 4: Column 1: 3 | Column 2: Vinschool-VinUni Scholarship | Column 3: 5% | Column 4: No requirements – automatic renewal | Column 5: \nRow 5: Column 1: 4 | Column 2: Vingroup Family Scholarship | Column 3: Adheres to the current policy in effect at the time of application. | Column 4: No requirements – automatic renewal | Column 5: \nRow 6: Column 1: 5 | Column 2: WIT (Woman in Tech) Scholarship | Column 3: 5% | Column 4: Automatic renewal if the main entry scholarship is maintained | Column 5: \nRow 7: Column 1: 6 | Column 2: Special Academic Scholarship | Column 3: 5% | Column 4: No requirements – automatic renewal | Column 5: \nRow 8: Column 1: 7 | Column 2: Education Development Aid | Column 3: 35% | Column 4: No requirements – automatic renewal | Column 5: \nRow 9: Column 1: 8 | Column 2: Need-based Financial Aid | Column 3: From 50% | Column 4: – Maintain the m inimum C GPA 2.0 (Marginal) in the academic year under evaluation (calculated as the average of the two main semesters : Fall and Spring ). – Complete the E . X . C . E . L self-evaluation and meet with the Advisor to discuss on the self-evaluation . | Column 5:", "content_hash": "59034c1b281a249ba550351a57c415400c67d7f7632140cb4c45c40f85b7ac61"}, "metadata": {"source_kind": "financial_policy", "source_id": "4715ee79132259e78a7c5ab81fc89b9914b3a1691833352aae1f384368af4775", "canonical_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/all-policies/criteria-to-maintain-the-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support/", "document_title": "Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support", "domain": "policy.vinuni.edu.vn", "domain_type": "policy", "source_trust": "official_high", "category": "student_affairs", "subcategory": "financial", "parser_name": "crawler", "parser_version": "v3", "source_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/all-policies/criteria-to-maintain-the-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support/", "final_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/all-policies/criteria-to-maintain-the-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support/", "crawl_depth": 0, "discovered_from": "seed", "http_status": 200, "content_type": "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "mime_type": "text/html", "file_size_bytes": 49802, "fetched_at": "2026-06-20T03:07:49.301375+00:00", "robots_allowed": true, "requires_login": false, "noindex": false, "access_level": "public", "crawl_run_id": "2f55a9b8-0bc8-4015-8aac-656a596ffa66", "reference_number": "GDL-SAM-004-V2.1", "document_status": "Guidelines", "issuing_unit": "Student Affairs Management Office and Office of University Registrar", "issued_date": "Sep 04, 2025", "applying_for": "All VinUniversity", "security_classification": "Public", "pdf_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf", "link_count": 15}}, {"record_id": "49bb4d7927f26039bebd734f80893ff4dd3170a03b3e2ee625286974864bed37", "record_type": "table_record", "parent_doc_id": "4715ee79132259e78a7c5ab81fc89b9914b3a1691833352aae1f384368af4775", "source_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/all-policies/criteria-to-maintain-the-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support/", "title": "Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support", "data": {"table_id": "49e3311ae198e6e9b4eca7b9d75b53042214fb57b9caf54a20f0a4fca1ae0479", "caption": null, "headers": ["Revision", "Date", "Author / Editor", "Description"], "rows": [["V1.0", "Nov 20, 2024", "Developed by: Student Affairs Management Office and Office of University Registrar Reviewed by: Educational Affairs Committee Approved by: Provost", "First release"], ["V2.0", "Jun 12, 2025", "Developed by: Student Affairs Management Office and Office of Registrar Reviewed by: Educational Affairs Committee Approved by: Provost", "Update the policy title and explicitly define what constitutes “good disciplinary standing” for renewal purposes."], ["V2.1", "Sep 04, 2025", "Developed by: Student Affairs Management Office and Office of Registrar Reviewed by: Vice Provost of Academic Administration Approved by: President of the University Council", "3rd released"]], "row_count": 3, "column_count": 4, "section_path": ["Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support", "3. Criteria to maintain the entry merit-based scholarship and financial aid support", "Record of Changes"], "page_number": null, "rag_text": "Table: Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support\nColumns: Revision | Date | Author / Editor | Description\nRow 1: Revision: V1.0 | Date: Nov 20, 2024 | Author / Editor: Developed by: Student Affairs Management Office and Office of University Registrar Reviewed by: Educational Affairs Committee Approved by: Provost | Description: First release\nRow 2: Revision: V2.0 | Date: Jun 12, 2025 | Author / Editor: Developed by: Student Affairs Management Office and Office of Registrar Reviewed by: Educational Affairs Committee Approved by: Provost | Description: Update the policy title and explicitly define what constitutes “good disciplinary standing” for renewal pu