"table_id": "e067d31d39dbfabc22dec97236da76543d001317aad84d657589a41c48a5be7a"}}, {"record_id": "b9ec32d852a31ecf9f71b44a5bcd521d7c06dd276d70dacb854c3dc8c8eb1940", "record_type": "table_record", "parent_doc_id": "94f545a014dc15d83e81e1ce8a03af48f42984c2ed43d771a3c9a9151e08a14f", "source_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf", "title": "PDF table page 2", "data": {"table_id": "e328a26a9949beb64288829d52593f9979b0822d00c368a2123ef1afc6b5f8ac", "caption": null, "headers": ["No", "Name", "Type", "Renewal criteria", "Note"], "rows": [["1", "Merit-based\nScholarships", "Full & 100%", "Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintain a cumulative\nGPA of 3.2 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation.", "If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\ntwo options will be\nimplemented as below:\n(a) Automatic Downgrade\n(1 level - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied\nif the Academic Year\nGPA is between 0.0 - 2.49\n(below good academic\nstanding).\n(b) Maintain the\nscholarship with the\ncondition – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA\nis between 2.50 - 3.19\n(from good academic\nstanding and above),\napplicable for Full and\n100% scholarships.\nThe students will be granted\nan additional regular\nsemester to improve their\nacademic and E.X.C.E.L\nperformance. The GPA and\nE.X.C.E.L performance at\nthe point of re-assessment\nwill be used for further\nconsideration.\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration."]], "row_count": 1, "column_count": 5, "section_path": [], "page_number": 2, "rag_text": "Table: GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf page 2\nColumns: No | Name | Type | Renewal criteria | Note\nRow 1: No: 1 | Name: Merit-based\nScholarships | Type: Full & 100% | Renewal criteria: Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintain a cumulative\nGPA of 3.2 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation. | Note: If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\ntwo options will be\nimplemented as below:\n(a) Automatic Downgrade\n(1 level - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied\nif the Academic Year\nGPA is between 0.0 - 2.49\n(below good academic\nstanding).\n(b) Maintain the\nscholarship with the\ncondition – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA\nis between 2.50 - 3.19\n(from good academic\nstanding and above),\napplicable for Full and\n100% scholarships.\nThe students will be granted\nan additional regular\nsemester to improve their\nacademic and E.X.C.E.L\nperformance. The GPA and\nE.X.C.E.L performance at\nthe point of re-assessment\nwill be used for further\nconsideration.\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration.", "content_hash": "737f8a0d7bfce9ed4d227a454741637c62710d46c6a69d4608105a3fc7c4de00"}, "metadata": {"source_kind": "policy_pdf", "source_id": "94f545a014dc15d83e81e1ce8a03af48f42984c2ed43d771a3c9a9151e08a14f", "canonical_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/GDL