cord", "parent_doc_id": "94f545a014dc15d83e81e1ce8a03af48f42984c2ed43d771a3c9a9151e08a14f", "source_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf", "title": "PDF table page 3", "data": {"table_id": "df35762942013093ce93d993bf13184e72f914d2a9efe1c5f95f3e07d36a61be", "caption": null, "headers": ["2", "Merit-based\nScholarships", "50%; 60%;\n70%; 80%;\n90%", "Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintaining a cumulative\nGPA of 2.5 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation.", "If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\nfollowing option will be\nimplemented as below:\nAutomatic Downgrade (1\nlevel - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA is\nbetween 0.0 - 2.49 (below\ngood academic standing).\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration."], "rows": [["3", "Vinschool-\nVinUni\nScholarship", "5%", "No requirements - automatic\nrenewal", ""], ["4", "Vingroup Family\nScholarship", "Adheres to\nthe current\npolicy in\neffect at the\ntime of\napplication.", "No requirements - automatic\nrenewal", ""], ["5", "WIT (Woman in\nTech)\nScholarship", "5%", "Automatic renewal if the\nmain entry\nscholarship is maintained", ""], ["6", "Special\nAcademic\nScholarship", "5%", "No requirements - automatic\nrenewal", ""], ["7", "Education\nDevelopment\nAid", "35%", "No requirements - automatic\nrenewal", ""], ["8", "Need-based\nFinancial Aid", "From 50%", "- Maintain the minimum\nCGPA 2.0 (Marginal) in the\nacademic year under\nevaluation (calculated as\nthe average of the two main\nsemesters: Fall and Spring).\n- Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet with\nthe Advisor to discuss on the\nself-evaluation .", ""]], "row_count": 6, "column_count": 5, "section_path": [], "page_number": 3, "rag_text": "Table: GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf page 3\nColumns: 2 | Merit-based\nScholarships | 50%; 60%;\n70%; 80%;\n90% | Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintaining a cumulative\nGPA of 2.5 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation. | If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\nfollowing option will be\nimplemented as below:\nAutomatic Downgrade (1\nlevel - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA is\nbetween 0.0 - 2.49 (below\ngood academic standing).\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration.\nRow 1: 2: 3 | Merit-based\nScholarships: Vinschool-\nVinUni\nScholarship | 50%; 60%;\n70%; 80%;\n90%: 5% | Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintaining a cumulative\nGPA of 2.5 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation.: No requirements - automatic\nrenewal | If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\nfollowing option will be\nimplemented as below:\nAutomatic Downgrade (1\nlevel - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA is\nbetween 0.0 - 2.49 (below\ngood academic standing).\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration.: \nRow 2: 2: 4 | Merit-based\nScholarships: Vingroup Family\nScholarship | 50%; 60%;\n70%; 80%;\n90%: Adheres to\nthe current\npolicy in\neffect at the\ntime of\napplication. | Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintaining a cumulative\nGPA of 2.5 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation.: No requirements - automatic\nrenewal | If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\nfollowing option will be\nimplemented as below:\nAutomatic Downgrade (1\nlevel - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA is\nbetween 0.0 - 2.49 (below\ngood academic standing).\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration.: \nRow 3: 2: 5 | Merit-based\nScholarships: WIT (Woman in\nTech)\nScholarship | 50%; 60%;\n70%; 80%;\n90%: 5% | Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintaining a cumulative\nGPA of 2.5 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation.: Automatic renewal if the\nmain entry\nscholarship is maintained | If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\nfollowing option will be\nimplemented as below:\nAutomatic Downgrade (1\nlevel - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA is\nbetween 0.0 - 2.49 (below\ngood academic standing).\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration.: \nRow 4: 2: 6 | Merit-based\nScholarships: Special\nAcademic\nScholarship | 50%; 60%;\n70%; 80%;\n90%: 5% | Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintaining a cumulative\nGPA of 2.5 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation.: No requirements - automatic\nrenewal | If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\nfollowing option will be\nimplemented as below:\nAutomatic Downgrade (1\nlevel - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA is\nbetween 0.0 - 2.49 (below\ngood academic standing).\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration.: \nRow 5: 2: 7 | Merit-based\nScholarships: Education\nDevelopment\nAid | 50%; 60%;\n70%; 80%;\n90%: 35% | Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintaining a cumulative\nGPA of 2.5 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation.: No requirements - automatic\nrenewal | If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\nfollowing option will be\nimplemented as below:\nAutomatic Downgrade (1\nlevel - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA is\nbetween 0.0 - 2.49 (below\ngood academic standing).\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration.: \nRow 6: 2: 8 | Merit-based\nScholarships: Need-based\nFinancial Aid | 50%; 60%;\n70%; 80%;\n90%: From 50% | Renewal is contingent upon:\n1. Maintaining a cumulative\nGPA of 2.5 or higher in\nthe academic year under\nevaluation (calculated\nas the average of the two\nmain semesters: Fall\nand Spring).\n2. Maintain good\ndisciplinary standing:\nThe student must not\ncommit major misconduct\n(Tier 3) or extremely\nserious misconduct\n(Tier4) as per Student\nCode of Conduct and\nStudent Academic\nIntegrity.\n3. Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet\nwith the Advisor to\ndiscuss the self-\nevaluation.: - Maintain the minimum\nCGPA 2.0 (Marginal) in the\nacademic year under\nevaluation (calculated as\nthe average of the two main\nsemesters: Fall and Spring).\n- Complete the E.X.C.E.L\nself-evaluation and meet with\nthe Advisor to discuss on the\nself-evaluation . | If the student does not meet\nthe minimum requirement of\nacademic performance, the\nfollowing option will be\nimplemented as below:\nAutomatic Downgrade (1\nlevel - based on current\nscholarship scheme of the\nacademic year) – Applied if\nthe Academic Year GPA is\nbetween 0.0 - 2.49 (below\ngood academic standing).\nNote: Special cases may be\nreviewed by the Committee\nfor consideration.:", "content_hash": "c3923d09c5a30619ed474f05de21593648870727e0235ddc3782efbfb77d2f6a"}, "metadata": {"source_kind": "policy_pdf", "source_id": "94f545a014dc15d83e81e1ce8a03af48f42984c2ed43d771a3c9a9151e08a14f", "canonical_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf", "document_title": "GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf", "domain": "policy.vinuni.edu.vn", "domain_type": "policy", "source_trust": "official_high", "category": "student_affairs", "subcategory": "financial", "parser_name": "pdf", "parser_version": "v3", "source_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf", "final_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/GDL-SAM-004-V2.1_Guidelines-for-maintaining-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support_4.9.2025.pdf", "parent_url": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/all-policies/criteria-to-maintain-the-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support/", "crawl_depth": 1, "anchor_text": "Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support", "link_context": "You can download this document here: Guidelines for Maintaining Entry Scholarship and Financial Aid Support", "discovered_from": "https://policy.vinuni.edu.vn/all-policies/criteria-to-maintain-the-entry-scholarship-and-financial-aid-support/", "http_status": 200, "content_type": "application/pdf", "mime_type": "application/pdf", "file_size_bytes": 312421, "etag": "\"4c465-68b9625c-408064;;;\"", "last_modified_header": "Thu, 04 Sep 2025 09:56:44 GMT", "fetched_at": "2026-06-20T03:13:37.170572+00:00", "robots_allowed": true, "requires_login": false, "noindex": false, "access_level": "public", "crawl_run_id": "2f55a9b8-0bc8-4015-8aa